 Yamadaṇḍa  : m.: Name of the missile specially related to Yama. [See  Daṇḍa, Yāmya astra ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in right half of page p129  (+offset) in original book.

08)  याम्य अस्त्र|याम्य अस्त्र|यांय अस्त्र|yaamya astra|యామ్య అస్త్ర|ಯಾಮ್ಯ ಅಸ್ತ್ರ|p129
 Yāmya astra  : nt.: A missile special to Yama.<br><br>  Described as heavenly (divya) 12. 5. 14, and fierce (ghora) 7. 53. 43; Arjuna had received it from Yama 7. 53. 43; 12. 5. 13-14; Arjuna's collection of missiles (astragrāma) included among other missiles, Yāmya astra 5. 166. 32-33; (Bhīṣma, Droṇa and Yudhiṣṭhira also knew it); Droṇa used it agaisnt Yudhiṣṭhira in order to kill him (jighāṁsuḥ) but Yudhiṣṭhira repelled it apparently by using the same missile 7. 132. 29-30; Bhīṣma and Arjuna used it against each other at the time of the cattle-raid 4. 59. 21. [See  Yamadaṇḍa ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*3rd word in right half of page p129  (+offset) in original book.

09)  रक्षसाम् अस्त्राणि|रक्षसाम् अस्त्राणि|रक्षसां अस्त्राणि|rakShasaam astraaNi|రక్షసామ్ అస్త్రాణి|ರಕ್ಷಸಾಮ್ ಅಸ್ತ್ರಾಣಿ|p129
 Rakṣasām astrāṇi  : nt. pl.: Missiles special to Rakṣases.<br><br>  Arjuna was to learn these after reaching the residence of Indra 3. 164. 29-30.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*4th word in right half of page p129  (+offset) in original book.

