 Vāruṇa^1  : adj. (pl.): of the Pāśas of Varuṇa 12. 220. 18. [See  Pāśa ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*1st word in right half of page p139  (+offset) in original book.

03)  वारुण^2|वारुण|vaaruNa|వారుణ|ವಾರುಣ|p139
 Vāruṇa^2  : adj.: of Gāṇḍiva bow, originally belonging to Varuṇa.<br><br>  It is one of the three divine bows belonging to celestial beings (divyāni dhanūṁṣi divicāriṇām), the other two being Vijaya of Mahendra and Śārṅga of Viṣṇu 5. 155. 5-6. [See  Gāṇḍīva ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in right half of page p139  (+offset) in original book.

04)  वारुण^3|वारुण|vaaruNa|వారుణ|ವಾರುಣ|p139
 Vāruṇa^3  : adj. (du.): of the two quivers of Varuṇa.<br><br>  Described as heavenly (divyau) 5. 59. 12, (divyarūpau) 8. 57. 42; great (maheṣudhī) 1. 216. 7; 5. 59. 12; 8. 57. 42; inexhaustible (akṣayyau) 1. 216. 7; (akṣayau) 5. 59. 12; 8. 57. 42; full of arrows (śarapūrṇau) 5. 59. 12; Varuṇa gave them to Arjuna at the time of burning the Khāṇḍava forest (prādād vai…akṣayyau ca maheṣudhī) 1. 216. 7; according to Karṇa, however, these were given by Havyavāha (Agni) himself to Arjuna (maheṣudhī…havyavāhāt) 8. 57. 42. <br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*3rd word in right half of page p139  (+offset) in original book.<br><br> previous_page p138       next_page p140

