 Śarolbaṇa  : nt.: Name of a missile (so called because it produced, when released, excessive number of arrows ?).<br><br>  Used, among other missiles (astrapūga 3. 163. 31) by Arjuna against Kirāta (Śiva); Śiva swallowed all those astras (jagrāsa… tāni sarvāṇy astrāṇi) 3. 163. 32. [See  Śaravarṣa ].<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p148  (+offset) in original book.

03)  शाक्र अस्त्र|शाक्र अस्त्र|shaakra astra|శాక్ర అస్త్ర|ಶಾಕ್ರ ಅಸ್ತ್ರ|p148
