02)  सौपर्ण अस्त्र|सौपर्ण अस्त्र|sauparNa astra|సౌపర్ణ అస్త్ర|ಸೌಪರ್ಣ ಅಸ್ತ್ರ|p157
 Sauparṇa astra  : nt.: Name of a missile.<br><br>  It was used (prāduṣkṛ) by Suśarman to free the feet of his army which were tied up by the snakes released by the Nāga astra of Arjuna; from the Sauparṇa astra came out the Suparṇas which started eating up the snakes; then the snakes, seeing those birds, crept away and the army was freed from the ties on their feet 8. 37. 25-27; 21-22.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*1st word in right half of page p157  (+offset) in original book.

