 Pauṣya  : adj.: (of a yoga) related to the nakṣatra Puṣya.<br><br>  The sage Vyāsa asked first Yudhiṣṭhira to hold the hand (in marriage) of Kṛṣṇā since that was an auspicious day when the moon was going to have the Pauṣya yoga i. e. be in conjunction with Puṣya (adya puṇyāham uta pāṇḍaveya/adya pauṣyaṁ yogam upaiti candramāḥ) 1. 190. 5 (Nī., however, on Bom. Ed. 1. 198. 5: pauṣyaṁ puṣyaty aneneti taṁ na tu puṣyaṁ tasyāvaivāhikatvāt). [See  Puṣya ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p259  (+offset) in original book.

