06)  भृग्वङ्ग।?गिरसक|भृग्वङ्ग|?गिरसक|भृग्वंग|bhRgvaMga|girasaka|bhRgvanga|bhRigvanga|bhRugvanga|భృగ్వంగ|గిరసక|ಭೃಗ್ವಂಗ|ಗಿರಸಕ|p262
 Bhṛgvaṅga(?gi)rasaka  : adj.: of a certain period of time.<br><br>  Yudhiṣṭhira asked Bhīṣma the name of the sage who first conceived of the śrāddha ceremony, its appropriate time and nature, in the period that was influenced by the Bhṛgus and the Aṅgirases (kena saṁkalpitaṁ śrāddhaṁ kasmin kāle kimātmakam/bhṛgvaṅga(? gi)rasake kāle muninā katareṇa vā) 13. 91. 1 (Nī., however, on Bom. Ed. 13. 91. 1: bhṛgvaṅgirasake yadā bhṛgavo 'ṅgirasaś ca vartante nānye).<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*4th word in right half of page p262  (+offset) in original book.

