08)  कोलाहल|कोलाहल|kolaahala|కోలాహల|ಕೋಲಾಹಲ|p318
 Kolāhala  : m.: Name of a mountain.<br><br>  Described as having consciousness (cetanāyukta) 1. 57. 32; due to his love (kāmāt) for the river Śuktimatī, flowing by his side, the mountain blocked her course; then king Vasu struck the mountain with his foot; the stroke produced a hole in the mountain through which the blocked river began to flow again; the mountain begot a pair - a male and a female - on the river; the river, happy to get past the mountain, informed the king about the birth of two children 1. 57. 32-34.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*6th word in right half of page p318  (+offset) in original book.<br><br> previous_page p317       next_page p319

