02)  कोशेश्वरस्य तीर्थानि|कोशेश्वरस्य तीर्थानि|kosheshvara|kosheshvarasya tiirthaani|tiirthaani|kosheshvarasya teerthaani|teerthaani|కోశేశ్వర|కోశేశ్వరస్య తీర్థాని|తీర్థాని|ಕೋಶೇಶ್ವರ|ಕೋಶೇಶ್ವರಸ್ಯ ತೀರ್ಥಾನಿ|ತೀರ್ಥಾನಿ|p319
 Kośeśvarasya tīrthāni  : nt. (pl.): Name of a number of tīrthas (sacred to Kubera ?)<br><br>  Near the place Ambuvaśya; by bathing there (kośeśvarasya tīrtheṣu) one is freed of all diseases and is glorified in the world of Brahmadeva (sarvavyādhivinirmukto brahmaloke mahīyate) 3. 81. 46. [See  Kaubera^1, Kaubera^2 ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p319  (+offset) in original book.

03)  कौबेर^1|कौबेर|kaubera|కౌబేర|ಕೌಬೇರ|p319
 Kaubera^1  : nt.: Name of a tīrtha sacred to Kubera.<br><br>  God Ailabila (Kubera) became the lord of wealth (dhanādhipatyaṁ saṁprāptaḥ) by practising austerities at this tīrtha; while Kubera was at this tīrtha riches and treasures waited on him (tatrastham eva taṁ (i. e. ailabilam) rājan dhanāni nidhayas tathā/upatasthuḥ) 9. 46. 22-23; Balarāma visited this tīrtha, bathed there according to the rites, and gave wealth to Brāhmaṇas 9. 46. 23, 28. [See  Kaubera^2  and  Kośeśvarasya tīrthāni ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*3rd word in left half of page p319  (+offset) in original book.

