 Jāmbūnada  : nt.: Name of a lake.<br><br>  Located on the Uśīrabīja mountain in the north (yatra jāmbūnadaṁ saraḥ); king Marutta performed there his sacrifice 5. 109. 20, 19; described as holy (puṇya), clean (vimala), abounding in lotuses (kamalākara), and related to the mountain Himavant (haimavata) 5. 109. 21; the lake in person (the lake not named) waited on the brahmanical sage Jīmūta (jītūtasyātra viprarṣer upatasthe mahātmanaḥ/sākṣāt…kamalākaraḥ) 5. 109. 21.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in right half of page p356  (+offset) in original book.

