 Dharmapṛṣṭha  : nt.: Name of a sacred place. <br><br>  Dharma is always present there (yatra dharmo mahārāja nityam āste); by visiting this place one who has a composed mind (samāhitaḥ) gets the fruit of a horse sacrifice 3. 82. 87.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p369  (+offset) in original book.

