03)  प्रशस्ता|प्रशस्ता|prashasta|prashastaa|ప్రశస్త|ప్రశస్తా|ಪ್ರಶಸ್ತ|ಪ್ರಶಸ್ತಾ|p391
 Praśastā  : f.: Name of a river.<br><br>  Located in the south (cf. 3. 117. 18); described as most holy (puṇyatamā) and flowing to the ocean (samudragā) 3. 118. 2; Yudhiṣṭhira visited it along with his brothers and, after bathing there (āplutya), he satisfied manes and gods (saṁtarpayām āsa pitṝn surāṁś ca) and gave riches to the prominent among the Brāhmaṇas; from there he went to the river Godāvarī 3. 118. 3.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*3rd word in right half of page p391  (+offset) in original book.

