07)  रथावर्त|रथावर्त|rathaavarta|రథావర్త|ರಥಾವರ್ತ|p431
 Rathāvarta  : m.: Name of a sacred place.<br><br>  Situated to the right of the goddess at Dhūmāvatī (devyās tu dakṣiṇārdhena rathāvarto narādhipa); if one mounts on the Rathāvarta with faith and with controlled senses he gets the highest condition by the favour of Mahādeva (tatrāroheta…śraddadhāno jitendriyaḥ/mahādevaprasādād dhi gaccheta paramāṁ gatim//) 3. 82. 21; circumambulating it one should proceed to the tīrtha called Dhārā 3. 82. 22,<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*4th word in right half of page p431  (+offset) in original book.

08)  रमणी|रमणी|ramaNi|ramaNii|ramaNee|రమణి|రమణీ|ರಮಣಿ|ರಮಣೀ|p431
