 Ādityasya āśramaḥ  : m.: Name of an āśrama.<br><br>  The āśrama of the high-souled Āditya (sun), the store of lustre, situated near the Ādityatīrtha (ādityasyāśramo yatra tejorāśer mahātmanaḥ) 3. 81. 160. [See  Adityatīriha  Vol. I. 293-294]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p511  (+offset) in original book.

