 Mahendrasya Vaiśravaṇasya ca sadman  : nt.: The house of Mahendra (Indra) and Vaiśravaṇa (Kubera).<br><br>  The eastern direction is so called; it is guarded by Indra and Vaiśravaṇa; it was pointed out by Dhaumya to Yudhiṣṭhira holding him by his right hand (prācīṁ diśam abhiprekṣya maharṣir idam abravīt// …indravaiśravaṇāv etāṁ diśaṁ pāṇḍava rakṣataḥ/…etad āhur mahendrasya rājño vaisravaṇasya ca…sadma) 3. 160. 3, 5-6; it is adorned by mountains, forest regions and woods (parvataiś ca vanāntaiś ca kānanaiś copaśobhitām) 3. 160. 5; people, sages, Siddhas, Sādhyas and gods worship sun rising from there 3. 160. 7.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*4th word in left half of page p552  (+offset) in original book.

