 Vṛṣṇyandhakapura  : nt.: Another name of Dvārakā.<br><br>  When Śālva beseiged Dvārakā no one could go out or enter Vṛṣṇyandhakapura without stamped permission (na cāmudro 'bhiniryāti na cāmudraḥ praveśyate/ vṛṣṇyandhakapure rājaṁs tadā saubhasamāgame) 3. 16. 19; army having many elephants and horses was stationed along all the roads and squares of the town (anu rathyāsu sarvāsu catvareṣu ca kaurava/balaṁ babhūva rājendra prabhūtagajavājimat) 3. 16. 20. [See  Dvārakā ]<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*4th word in right half of page p570  (+offset) in original book.

