 Vaikhānasāśrama, Vaikhānasānām āśramaḥ  : m.: The āśrama where the Vaikhānasas lived. <br><br>  A.   Location: Situated in the north (asyāṁ diśi variṣṭhāyām uttarāyām) 5. 109. 3. <br><br>  B.   Holiness: One of the holy and sanctified places in the west mentioned by Dhaumya (pratīcyām…diśi/yāni tatra pavitrāṇi puṇyāny āyatanāni ca) 3. 87. 1; the āśrama was dear to the Vaikhānasa sages who had obtained perfection (vaikhānasānāṁ siddhānāṁ ṛṣīṇām āśramaḥ priyaḥ) 3. 87. 13. <br><br>  C.   Past event: It was pointed out by Suparṇa to Gālava (atra vaikhānasāśramaḥ) 5. 109. 9.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*1st word in left half of page p571  (+offset) in original book.

