04)  शङ्कुकर्णेश्वर|शङ्कुकर्णेश्वर|शंकुकर्णेश्वर|shaMkukarNeshvara|shankukarNeshvara|శంకుకర్ణేశ్వర|ಶಂಕುಕರ್ಣೇಶ್ವರ|p572
 Śaṅkukarṇeśvara  : m.: Name of a holy place. <br><br>  Close to the famous tīrtha called Dṛmi 3. 80. 87; wise men say that by worshipping god Śaṅkukarṇeśvara (Śiva) at this place one got tenfold fruit of performing an Aśvamedha sacrifice (aśvamedhaṁ daśaguṇaṁ pravadanti manīṣiṇaḥ) 3. 80. 87.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*4th word in right half of page p572  (+offset) in original book.<br><br> previous_page p571       next_page p573

