 Kākṣa  : m. (pl.): Name of a Janapada.<br><br>  One of the (northern) Janapadas (also called Deśas (uddeśamātreṇa mayā deśāḥ saṁkīrtitāḥ 6. 10. 68) of the Bhāratavarṣa listed by Saṁjaya (ata ūrdhvaṁ janapadān nibodha gadato mama) 6. 10. 37, 5; (kākṣāḥ sāmudraniṣkuṭāḥ) 6. 10. 47.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*3rd word in right half of page p652  (+offset) in original book.

