 Kāraskara  : m. (pl.): Name of a people.<br><br>  Duryodhana saw Kāraskaras and some other peoples in the residence of Yudhiṣṭhira as if they were made slaves and were under his control (āvarjitā ivābhānti nighnāś …/kāraskarā…yudhiṣṭiraniveśane) 2. 46. 21 (Nī. on Bom. Ed. 2. 50. 20: āvarjitāḥ dāsavad vaśagāḥ); a certain Rākṣasī told a pilgrim that one should avoid Kāraskaras who followed wrong dharma (kāraskarān …durdharmāṁś ca vivarjayet//iti tīrthānusartāraṁ rākṣasī kācid abravīt) 8. 30. 45-46. <br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p656  (+offset) in original book.

