 Tālajaṅgha  : m. (pl.): Name of some Kṣatriyas.<br><br>  Past events: (1) King Sagara extirpated them along with Haihayas 3. 104. 7; (2) King Bakula of the Tālajaṅghas was one of the sixteen kings who completely annihilated their kinsmen, friends and relatives (ye samuccicchidur jñātīn suhṛdaś ca sabāndhavān) 5. 72. 13, 11; (3) To illustrate that the lustre and strength of the Kṣatriyas was pacified when they faced Brāhmaṇas, Bhīṣma mentioned that the Bhṛgus had conquered Tālajaṅghas 13. 34. 15-16; Aurva (a Bhārgava) alone destroyed a large number of Tālajaṅgha Kṣatriyas (tālajaṅghaṁ mahat kṣatram aurveṇaikena nāśitam) 13. 138. 11.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p734  (+offset) in original book.

