 Pulindaka  : m. (pl.): Name of a Janapada.<br><br>  Listed separately from Pulinda by Saṁjaya among the northern Janapadas (also called Deśas 6. 10. 68) of Bhāratavarṣa (ata ūrdhvaṁ janapadān nibodha) 6. 10. 37, 5; (sindhupulindakāḥ) 6. 10. 39. [See  Pulinda ].<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*1st word in left half of page p788  (+offset) in original book.

