 Mahaujas  : m. (pl.): Name of a people.<br><br>  Varapra, the king of Mahaujas people, listed by Bhīmasena among the eighteen kings who in the past extirpated their kinsmen, friends and relatives (aṣṭādaśeme rājānaḥ…/ye samuccicchidur jñātīn suhṛdaś ca sabāndhavān//) 5. 72. 11; (varapraś ca mahaujasām) 5. 72. 15.<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*4th word in right half of page p831  (+offset) in original book.

