01)  रोमश|रोमश|romasha|రోమశ|ರೋಮಶ|p854
 Romaśa  : m. (pl.): Name of a people.<br><br>  Mentioned by Duryodhana along with Śakas, Tukhāras and others who brought as tribute for the Rājasūya an arbuda of horses of high breed and going long distances and also a padma of gold to be counted by crores; even then they were stopped at the gate and were not allowed to enter (…romaśāḥ…/mahāgamān dūragamān gaṇitān arbudaṁ hayān// koṭiśaś caiva bahuśaḥ suvarṇaṁ padmasaṁmitam/balim ādāya vividhaṁ dvāri tiṣṭhanti vāritāḥ//) 2. 47. 26-27 (Are these Romans ? See  Romā  Cul. Ind. Vol. II. p. 559 and  Roman  above).<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*1st word in left half of page p854  (+offset) in original book.

02)  रौद्र|रौद्र|raudra|రౌద్ర|ರೌದ್ರ|p854
