 Śaradaṇḍa  : m. (pl. ?): Name of a country.<br><br>  The horses of this country were referred to as śaradaṇḍaja; these horses were yoked to the chariot of Daṇḍaketu (śaradaṇḍānudaṇḍajāḥ/…daṇḍaketum udāvahan) 7. 22. 58 [See Editor's note on the stanza, Cr. Edn. Vol. 9, pp. 1147-1148: “…Śaradaṇḍa and Anudaṇḍa would be names of different countries. We know nothing of Anudaṇḍa, but Śaradaṇḍa was the name of a country belonging to Śālva in Madhyadeśa (Kāśikā on Pāṇini IV. 1. 173: śaradaṇḍāś ca śālvāvayavasaṁjñitāḥ)”].<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*1st word in left half of page p882  (+offset) in original book.

