 Saptadvīpa  : m., nt. (sg.): Name of some country to the north of Khāṇḍavaprastha ?<br><br>  Arjuna in his expedition to the north (diśaṁ dhanapater iṣṭām 2. 23. 9) before the Rājasūya conquered the kings of the Saptadvīpa (saptadvīpe ca ye nṛpāḥ) 2. 23. 16 (this can impossibly refer to the seven Dvīpas of this earth cf. 6. 12. 4; 12. 49. 31).<br><br><br>_______________________________<br>*2nd word in left half of page p903  (+offset) in original book.

03)  समक्ष|समक्ष|samakSha|సమక్ష|ಸಮಕ್ಷ|p903
